form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, N-4-5

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/25/2023 U. S. Department of Homeland Security OMB No. 1115-0052 Citizenship & Immigration Services Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony AR: 071 829 679 Date: May 05, 2005 JULIA AMELIA LOPEZ mailed wit 12719 GROVETREE AVE. DOWNEY CA 90242 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony on: THURSDAY, MAY 19, 2005 at: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT 312 NORTH SPRING STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 COURT ROOM #329, 3RD FLOOR Please report promptly at 12:30 P.M. You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE OTHER SIDE ANSWERED IN INK OR ON A TYPEWRITER. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit, or Refugee Travel Document. Any Immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is on behalf of your child(children), bring your child (children). Other NO CAMERAS OR CELL PHONES ALLOWED IN THE COURTHOUSE. PLEASE BRING A WHEELCHAIR IF YOU CANNOT STAND FOR LONG OR WALK LONG DISTANCES If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, you will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445 (Rev. 1/8/92) (SEE OTHER SIDE)
